5|$|Japanese {{music is}} eclectic and diverse. Many instruments, {{such as the}} koto, were {{introduced}} in the 9th and 10th centuries. The accompanied recitative of the Noh drama dates from the 14th century and the popular folk music, with the guitar-like shamisen, from the sixteenth. Western classical music, introduced in the late 19th century, now forms {{an integral part of}} <b>Japanese</b> <b>culture.</b> The imperial court ensemble Gagaku has influenced the work of some modern Western composers.|$|E
